Date:  15/2/1890
Source:  Oxford Observer
Author:

Vol / Page:  4
Edition:
Quote:  Where the weka once roamed in the brown tussock, disturbed only by the bark of the musterers' [sic] dog or the crack of the stockman's whip, are to be seen bright homely cottages and neat gardens, churches, schools, public halls, hotels, a Bank, and a printing office, evidences of progress on every hand, and proof enough that no lazy people are living here.
